    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Rhubarb, in Edinburgh, was one of the most memorable restaurant experiences I have ever had.  My parents treated me when I was going to school there.  Other than during their visit, the most memorable food I had came from my international roommates in our ill-equipped kitchen flat.  I did drink a lot of tea at Elephant House- I second that recommendation (where J.K. Rowling wrote the first Harry Potter!).  I&#39;m planning a trip back for this summer so I hope to hear about places you visit!  Yay for Edinburgh!!!</p>
    </div>

